# VENTD TEST MASTERPLAN — Coverage, Invariants, Issue Detection

**Document purpose:** This is the authoritative test-suite design for ventd. It is a companion to `ventdmasterplan.md` — every feature task in the main plan has a matching test task here, and the test plan also owns standalone test tracks that aren't tied to specific features (fuzzing, chaos, regression, supply chain). Written for Cowork to generate Claude Code prompts and review the resulting test PRs.

Relationship to the main plan: the main-plan task catalogue in §8 adds code; this plan's task catalogue in §17 adds tests. Where a feature task (e.g. `P1-HAL-01`) has a corresponding test task (`T-HAL-01`), the test task is ready only after the feature task is merged. Test tasks that are pure infrastructure (fixture libraries, CI jobs, fuzz corpora) can start in parallel with Phase 0 of the main plan.

---

## 0 · Glossary

Same as main plan. Additions:

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Invariant** | A property that must always hold. Bound 1:1 to a named subtest so a regression fails at a predictable location. Example: "PWM writes are clamped to `[MinPWM, MaxPWM]`." |
| **Rule file** | A `.claude/rules/*.md` markdown file enumerating invariants. Each rule has an ID; each ID maps to exactly one subtest. |
| **Fixture** | A reusable hardware or environment mock (fake sysfs tree, stub IPMI BMC, stub USB HID device, stub WMI provider). |
| **Replay test** | A regression test named after a GitHub issue number (`TestRegression_Issue118_*`) that encodes the bug's conditions and asserts they stay fixed. |
| **Golden** | A committed reference output (YAML, JSON, diff) that tests compare against. Update via explicit `-update` flag. |
| **HIL** | Hardware-in-loop. Runs on real hardware in `validation/`. Not gating CI; gating release. |

---

## 1 · Test architecture — the layering model

Ventd tests live in five tiers. A PR that adds a feature lands tests in the tiers that apply; tiers below it must already be green.

```
  Tier 5 — Release validation (HIL, cross-OS smoke)       validation/
           Manual, pre-release only.
  Tier 4 — End-to-end (browser, full daemon)              internal/web/e2e_*
           go-rod headless Chromium. Gates PRs via e2e.yml.
  Tier 3 — Integration (multi-package, fixtures)          internal/*/integration_*
           Fake sysfs, fake IPMI, fake HID. Gates PRs.
  Tier 2 — Unit + property + fuzz                         internal/*/<pkg>_test.go
           Fast. Runs on every test invocation. Gates PRs.
  Tier 1 — Static analysis                                vet, lint, staticcheck, vulncheck
           Runs before tests.
```

Rules:

- A feature cannot regress a tier it previously passed. If Tier 4 was green and now fails, the feature PR is rejected regardless of Tier 2 status.
- New tiers never appear. If a test doesn't fit a tier, escalate.
- Each tier has a dedicated CI job; failure in any tier fails the PR.

