## 2 · Invariant binding — generalise the hwmon-safety pattern

Ventd already has one working invariant file (`.claude/rules/hwmon-safety.md`) bound 1:1 to `internal/controller/safety_test.go:TestSafety_Invariants`. This pattern is extended to every safety-critical surface.

Rule files to own (each is a markdown file under `.claude/rules/`):

| File | Owned by suite | Scope |
|---|---|---|
| `hwmon-safety.md` | `internal/controller/safety_test.go:TestSafety_Invariants` | PWM clamping, pwm_enable restore, stop-fan gates, panic mode (exists) |
| `calibration-safety.md` | `internal/calibrate/safety_test.go:TestCalSafety_Invariants` | ZeroPWMSentinel, fingerprint fences, checkpoint atomicity, abort semantics |
| `watchdog-safety.md` | `internal/watchdog/safety_test.go:TestWDSafety_Invariants` | Restore runs on every exit path, per-fan panic recovery, fallback to firmware-auto |
| `hal-contract.md` | `internal/hal/contract_test.go:TestHAL_Contract` | Every backend obeys: Enumerate is idempotent, Read never writes, Write clamps, Restore is safe on unopened channels, Caps is stable |
| `ipmi-safety.md` | `internal/hal/ipmi/safety_test.go` | ioctl timeout, retry backoff, no uncontrolled manual-mode entry, fallback to firmware auto on daemon exit |
| `liquid-safety.md` | `internal/hal/liquid/safety_test.go` | USB disconnect mid-write never leaves pump below `pump_minimum`, reconnect re-arms safely |
| `pi-stability.md` | `internal/curve/pi_safety_test.go` | Integral anti-windup bounded, gain bounds enforced, fallback on NaN |
| `mpc-stability.md` | `internal/curve/mpc_safety_test.go` | Solver always returns feasible in ≤ 10 ms, residual fallback to PI, model persistence is atomic |
| `acoustic-safety.md` | `internal/acoustic/safety_test.go` | Microphone capture never blocks the control loop, FFT bounded memory, false-positive rate capped |
| `config-schema.md` | `internal/config/schema_test.go:TestSchema_Invariants` | Every config field has a validator; every validator has a rejecting fixture |
| `web-security.md` | `internal/web/security_invariants_test.go` | CSRF, CSP, rate limit, TLS, path traversal, constant-time compare |

Rule file format:

```
# <Scope> Invariants
Each rule below is bound 1:1 to a subtest in <file>:<function>.
Editing a rule requires editing the corresponding subtest in the
same PR. Adding a rule requires landing the subtest in the same PR.

## RULE-<ID>: <one-line invariant>
<paragraph explaining the invariant, why it holds, what fails if it doesn't>
Bound: <file>:<subtest_name>

## RULE-<ID>: ...
```

Enforcement: a CI lint (T-META-01) parses every rule file, confirms every `Bound:` line points to a real subtest, and fails if any rule is unbound or any subtest exists without a rule.

