## 3 · Fixture library

Every backend gets a reusable fixture under `internal/testfixture/<backend>/`. Tests import them; they are not duplicated per-test.

| Fixture | Package | Fakes | Consumers |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fakehwmon` | `internal/testfixture/fakehwmon` | `/sys/class/hwmon/hwmonN/` trees with configurable pwm/fan/temp/chip-name/pwm_enable | controller, calibrate, hwmon, monitor, setup, watchdog |
| `fakeipmi` | `internal/testfixture/fakeipmi` | Stubbed `/dev/ipmi0` via named-pipe + ioctl table; returns canned sensor/SDR responses for Supermicro/Dell/HPE | hal/ipmi, watchdog (IPMI restore) |
| `fakeliquid` | `internal/testfixture/fakeliquid` | USB HID mock with Corsair Commander Core / NZXT X3 / Lian Li UNI Hub protocols | hal/liquid |
| `fakecrosec` | `internal/testfixture/fakecrosec` | `/dev/cros_ec` stub; implements EC_CMD_* responses | hal/crosec |
| `fakepwmsys` | `internal/testfixture/fakepwmsys` | `/sys/class/pwm/pwmchipN/pwmN` tree | hal/pwmsys |
| `fakenvml` | `internal/testfixture/fakenvml` | purego-loadable shim; returns canned NVML responses; gated by build tag | nvidia, monitor |
| `fakewmi` | `internal/testfixture/fakewmi` | Stub Windows WMI provider via embedded JSON-fed fake | hal/windows (cross-compile build only) |
| `fakesmc` | `internal/testfixture/fakesmc` | IOKit stub returning SMC key/value pairs | hal/macos (cross-compile build only) |
| `fakemic` | `internal/testfixture/fakemic` | Signal-generator producing synthetic fan acoustics with configurable blade-pass + bearing defects | acoustic |
| `fakedmi` | `internal/testfixture/fakedmi` | `/sys/class/dmi/id/*` tree, known board fingerprints (MSI MEG X570, Gigabyte X870E Aorus, ASUS Prime X670E, Supermicro X11, Dell PowerEdge R750, Framework 13/16, RPi 5, MacBook Pro 14 Asahi) | hwdb, setup, autoload |
| `fakedbus` | `internal/testfixture/fakedbus` | Abstract-socket D-Bus endpoint returning StartUnit/StopUnit canned responses | modprobe, hal/ipmi, watchdog |
| `fakeuevent` | `internal/testfixture/fakeuevent` | AF_NETLINK pair writing canned kernel messages | hwmon/watcher |
| `faketime` | `internal/testfixture/faketime` | Monotonic clock override for deterministic timer tests | calibrate, controller, watchdog, acoustic |
| `fakecfg` | `internal/testfixture/fakecfg` | Builder that yields known-good and known-bad configs for round-tripping | config, setup, web |

Fixture rules:

- Every fixture has a `New*(t *testing.T, opts *Options)` constructor that wires cleanup via `t.Cleanup()`.
- Fixtures must be deterministic: no wallclock, no `rand.Float64()` without a seeded source, no real network.
- Fixtures must be race-clean; `go test -race ./...` must pass with every fixture exercised.
- No real hardware I/O. If a backend's logic is unreachable without real hardware, the untested path is documented in `COVERAGE.md` and covered in Tier 5 HIL only.

