## 4 · Fuzzing & property-based tests

Fuzz targets, each using Go native fuzzing (`f.Fuzz`):

| Target | Package | Corpus seed | Invariant |
|---|---|---|---|
| `FuzzConfigParse` | internal/config | `testdata/fuzz/config_*` + every validation fixture | Parse never panics; parse-serialise-reparse is stable |
| `FuzzYAMLMigrate` | internal/config | Every version of config.example.yaml across tags | Migrate always produces a valid current-schema config |
| `FuzzIPMIResponse` | internal/hal/ipmi | Recorded BMC responses (Supermicro, Dell) + random bit-flips | Parse never panics; unknown fields logged not crashed |
| `FuzzHIDReport` | internal/hal/liquid | Recorded reports from each supported device + random noise | Parse never panics; out-of-range values clamp |
| `FuzzExprCurve` | internal/curve | Malicious expressions (infinite loops, huge allocs, nested refs) | Bounded eval; rejects cleanly |
| `FuzzDMIFingerprint` | internal/hwdb | Synthesised DMI trees including UTF-8 and control chars | Match never panics; anonymiser strips PII |
| `FuzzMpcModel` | internal/curve | Random ARX coefficients + synthetic thermal traces | Solver returns finite, feasible PWM in ≤ 10 ms |
| `FuzzModulesAlias` | internal/hwmon | Real `/lib/modules/*/modules.alias` files + malformed | Parser reports expected modules without panic |
| `FuzzChipName` | internal/config | Random chip-name strings including Unicode | EnrichChipName never crashes; idempotent |
| `FuzzUeventFrame` | internal/hwmon | Real AF_NETLINK captures + truncated/padded variants | No panic; watcher stays responsive |
| `FuzzSetupToken` | internal/web | Random byte strings for setup-token compare | Constant-time compare; no timing oracle (verify via `-count` histogram) |
| `FuzzACPIParse` | internal/hal/windows | Synthesised ACPI table bytes (cross-compiled) | No panic |
| `FuzzSMCKey` | internal/hal/macos | SMC key wire frames | No panic; unknown keys reported not crashed |

Property tests (using `testing/quick` or `gopter`):

| Property | Package | Claim |
|---|---|---|
| `PropCurveMonotonicNonDecreasing` | internal/curve | For `linear`/`points` curves, `tempA ≤ tempB ⇒ evaluate(tempA) ≤ evaluate(tempB)` |
| `PropCurveClamped` | internal/curve | Output ∈ `[0, 100]` for every input |
| `PropSmoothingConvergence` | internal/controller | EMA output converges to a constant input within `5·τ` |
| `PropPIStability` | internal/curve | For any `(Kp, Ki)` within config bounds and step disturbance, integral bounded ≤ IntegralClamp |
| `PropHysteresisNoFlutter` | internal/controller | Within deadband, output is identical across a sensor oscillation |
| `PropMPCFeasibility` | internal/curve | Solver always returns a value within `[MinPWM, MaxPWM]`, even on degenerate models |
| `PropDitherMean` | internal/controller | Sum of dither offsets across fans bound to same curve ≈ 0 over time |
| `PropConfigRoundtrip` | internal/config | Parse(Serialise(c)) == c for every valid c |
| `PropHWDBDeterministic` | internal/hwdb | Match(fp) is a pure function: same input → same output |

Each fuzz target runs for `-fuzztime=10s` in CI on PR, and for `10m` nightly. Corpora are committed at `internal/*/testdata/fuzz/`. Nightly finds that trip a new crasher are committed as PRs to grow the corpus.

