## 5 · Chaos / fault injection

Fault-injection wrappers let tests simulate every realistic hardware failure. All injection is via a `faultfs.FS` interface that wraps the real or fake filesystem; the production code takes an `fs.FS`-like abstraction (already needed for the HAL abstraction in the main plan, so no extra wiring).

| Injection | Where | Tests |
|---|---|---|
| EIO on first N writes, then success | fakehwmon | Controller retry path; watchdog fallback on repeated failure |
| ETIMEDOUT on read | fakehwmon, fakeipmi | Controller skip-tick; calibration settle-timeout |
| Partial write (short write) | fakehwmon | Controller detects torn write and retries |
| ENOSPC on checkpoint | fakefile | Calibrate surfaces error without corrupting previous checkpoint |
| Slow I/O (100ms latency) | faketime + fakehwmon | Hot loop doesn't stall past poll interval |
| USB disconnect mid-frame | fakeliquid | Liquid backend pumps above `pump_minimum`; re-arms on reconnect |
| BMC returns completion code 0xC3 (busy) | fakeipmi | Backend retries with exponential backoff, caps at 3 |
| Kernel sends ENOBUFS on AF_NETLINK | fakeuevent | Watcher continues via fallback poll |
| modprobe exits non-zero | fakemodprobe | Autoload surfaces error to diag without crashing |
| Config file truncated mid-YAML | fakefile | Load error is clear; daemon falls back to last-good if applicable |
| Setup token file missing | fakefile | Daemon regenerates token, logs clearly |
| NVML dlopen returns nil | fakenvml | GPU features disabled silently; no panic |
| OOM during MPC solve | `testing.AllocsPerRun` | Solver falls back to PI |
| Clock skew during calibration | faketime | Calibration step times out correctly regardless of wallclock jumps |
| `/sys` re-enumeration mid-tick (hwmon renumber) | fakehwmon | Controller re-resolves via ChipName; no fan stalled |

Chaos suite sits at `internal/chaos/` and runs as a separate CI job (`chaos.yml`) to keep signal-to-noise high. Tier-3 level.

