## 6 · Concurrency testing

Every test package imports `go.uber.org/goleak`. `TestMain` wrappers assert zero goroutine leaks.

Race-specific suites:

| Suite | Verifies |
|---|---|
| `TestRace_ConfigHotReload` | SIGHUP mid-tick doesn't torn-read config; atomic.Pointer swap ordering |
| `TestRace_CalibrateVsController` | Calibration starts, controller yields, calibration finishes, controller resumes without double-writing PWM |
| `TestRace_PanicVsTick` | Panic button engages mid-tick; controller respects panic gate within 1 tick |
| `TestRace_WatchdogRestore` | Restore concurrent with tick; last write is deterministic |
| `TestRace_WebSSEBroadcast` | 100 SSE subscribers; buildStatus called once per cadence, not N times |
| `TestRace_HotplugDuringCalibrate` | uevent fires mid-calibration; calibration fingerprint-check prevents cross-contamination |
| `TestRace_FleetGossip` | 10 nodes gossip concurrently; membership converges within 10s (sim clock) |

All run under `-race`. Alpine lane's `-race` skip is lifted for pure-Go packages (only external-cgo-dep packages are exempt).

Deadlock detection: `TestDeadlock_*` suites run under `-timeout=30s` and a `runtime/deadlock` build-tag variant that converts `sync.Mutex` to `deadlock.Mutex` for diagnosis. Not gating CI; runs nightly.

