## 11 · Regression / issue replay

Every closed GitHub issue that represented a real bug gets a replay test. Naming: `TestRegression_Issue<N>_<short_slug>`.

The pattern:

1. Reproduce the exact conditions of the bug (fixture, input, sequence).
2. Assert the correct behaviour.
3. Commit the test in the same PR that fixes the issue; the test must fail before the fix and pass after.

A CI lint (T-META-02) scans for every closed issue with `type: bug` and verifies `grep -r "Issue<N>_" internal/ cmd/` returns a hit. Issues labeled `no-regression-test` are exempt with an explanation in the issue.

